<div id="review_10693521" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/10693521" />
    <a title="Hot Diggity Dan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/699380-hot-diggity-dan"><img alt="Hot Diggity Dan" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/10693521?book_show_action=true">Dec 19, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hot Diggity Dan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hot Diggity Dan" href="/user/show/699380-hot-diggity-dan">Hot Diggity Dan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer10693521" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7381373425023207406">An extremely compelling and well ordered chronicle. The translation is a little rote at times, leaning more toward the literal than I would prefer. The Latin probably has much more imbued meaning that the editor effectively mutes with rote phrasology like &quot;in order that&quot; for &quot;ut&quot;. Any intermediate Latinist will share that gripe. <br/><br/>As for the history, it is a remarkably complex feud between rival Flemish factions in the 12th century and makes for an excellent resource in the study of regional vs. l</span>
  <span id="freeText7381373425023207406" style="display:none">An extremely compelling and well ordered chronicle. The translation is a little rote at times, leaning more toward the literal than I would prefer. The Latin probably has much more imbued meaning that the editor effectively mutes with rote phrasology like "in order that" for "ut". Any intermediate Latinist will share that gripe. <br /><br />As for the history, it is a remarkably complex feud between rival Flemish factions in the 12th century and makes for an excellent resource in the study of regional vs. local feudal ordering--particularly in respect to its Flemish context, and the Low Lands' later affinity for republican democracy. <br /><br />All in all, one of the best primary sources I read in all of college.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7381373425023207406" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


